                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote script="cursivaAntiquior">Anglicana; the same hand as British Library, Add MS 89790, olim Warminster (Wilts.), Longleat House, Marquess of Bath MS 29, attributed by O'Byrne to <persName role="scr" key="person_898">Nicholas Bellewe</persName>. ‘<persName key="person_5120">Ion Flemmyn</persName>’ in rubricator’s red (fol. 62), taken in earlier literature as the scribe's name but believed by O'Byrne to be the rubricator.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="flourInit">At the openings of the texts, three-line blue lombards with red flourishing; two-line examples at lesser divisions. A few red and blue line-fillers at chapter ends, the text occasionally divided by red or blue paraphs. Headings in the text hand and ink.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notAfter="1500" notBefore="1400">
                        <p>Whittawed leather over rounded wooden boards, s. xv, sewn on four thongs. Scars from a central strap seating and from a seating for its pin in the middle of the lower board. At the front, the raised pastedown of the current binding, followed by a blank six-leaf quire (fols i–vii); at the rear, a quire of four, probably cut from a single folio of a Latin manuscript in double columns (fols 67–70).</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
